                      <div class="elementStandard elementContent elementHeadline elementHeadline_var0" id="anchor_41d90a1a_SMA">
                                                  <h1>
                            SMA                                                      </h1>
                                              </div>
                      <div class="elementStandard elementContent elementHeadline elementHeadline_var0" id="anchor_08131f23_Stone-Mastic-Asphalt">
                                                  <h2>
                            Stone Mastic Asphalt                                                      </h2>
                                              </div>
                      <div class="elementClearer"> </div>
                      <div class="elementClearerWithSpace spacer2"> </div>
                      <div class="elementStandard elementContent elementText elementText_var0">
                        <p>Increasing traffic volumes, higher axle loads, changes in our climate  − the challenges road construction experts around the globe have to face.<br/><br/>Stone Mastic Asphalt (SMA) has shown its outstanding performance on a variety of road surfaces throughout the world for more than 40 years − making SMA one of the most popular surfaces courses used.<br/><br/>SMA is based on the concept of a self-supporting stone skeleton, with a thick mastic and high binder content. This is made possible by using high performance fiber pellets. The low void content makes the compacted layer practically impermeable to water.</p><ul><li>safe</li><li>versatile</li><li>durable</li><li>sustainable</li><li>economic</li></ul><p>With these features, SMA fulfils all the requirements of modern infrastructure  − offering its benefits to road users, local authorities and the asphalt industry alike.<br/></p>                      </div>
